          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Three samples were used. The samples consisted of",
                "polished pyrolytic graphite with a sputter-deposited Al",
                "layer on top- 3.3*E+18 at/cm**2, 27*E+18 at/cm**2,",
                "58*E+18 at/cm**2, respectively. On top of the aluminum",
                "a thin Au layer with a thickness of 7.7*E+16 at/cm**2",
                "was evaporated, and on top of the gold a Be layer with",
                "a thickness of 4.4*E+18 at/cm**2. The purpose of the Al",
                "layers was to shift the signal of the C substrate",
                "towards lower energies in order to separate it from the",
                "Be signal, so that the Be signal could be measured more",
                "precisely with smaller background contribution from the",
                "substrate."
              ]
            }
          ],
